race.comment: CHARTWELL HOUSE (1) hasn't struck a blow in this debut prep for Aaron Laing, but this shapes as by far his most winnable assignment in a long time. The draw will look a lot better if a few of the emergencies don't gain a start and he gets in nicely after the claim for Liana Wood, who gets a great chance at a first career win. SWEET CHEVAL (7) a chance given that, although terrible last start, he got within a head of WARMOSA three back at Colac. MR CHARISMATIC (5) has a horror gate to contend with here but is a first-up winner in the past and has been performing adequately at the jumpouts for a race like this. MIGHTY FEAT (8) had a gap between runs last start, so expect him to have come on from that and he has drawn well.
